 Recognize that the original series has two separate series. Since we have two separate series, we need to find a way to combine them. We will do so by finding a common denominator.
```latex
\begin{align*}
\sum_{j = 1}^\infty \sum_{k = 1}^\infty \frac{1}{(j + k)^3} &= \sum_{j = 1}^\infty \sum_{k = 1}^\infty \frac{1}{j^3 k^3} \\
&= \sum_{j = 1}^\infty \sum_{k = 1}^\infty \frac{1}{j^3} \cdot \frac{1}{k^3}
\end{align*}
```
